law.text:
There shall be appointed by the Governor a State Advisory Committee for Educational Improvement in accordance with the following:
The State Advisory Committee for Educational Improvement shall be eighteen (18) members broadly representative of citizens, parents, teachers, and administrators. Their principal duties shall be to advise the Governor, the State Board for Elementary and Secondary Education, and the department on the implementation of the provisions of KRS 158.650 to 158.710 and KRS 158.6453 and 158.6455.
All members shall be voting members appointed by the Governor and shall serve terms of four (4) years, except that the original appointments will be made as follows:
Five (5) members for four (4) year terms;
Five (5) members for three (3) year terms;
Four (4) members for two (2) year terms; and
Four (4) members for a one (1) year term.
The State Advisory Committee for Educational Improvement shall elect a chairman annually from its membership;
The members shall be remunerated for actual and necessary expenses incurred while attending meetings of the State Advisory Committee for Educational Improvement or while serving in the capacity as representative of the State Advisory Committee for Educational Improvement.
The State Advisory Committee for Educational Improvement shall meet at least three (3) times each year at times and places as it determines by resolution.
